OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F304A1781067873
OL,3,CPoorest families must spend 85% of
OL,4,Cdisposable income to get healthy diet
OL,5,C` study
OL,7,FThe poorest families with children
OL,8,Fneed to spend 85% of their disposable
OL,9,Fincome to afford a healthy diet,
OL,10,Faccording to an annual report.
OL,12,FHealthier food is nearly twice as
OL,13,Fexpensive per calorie as less healthy
OL,14,Falternatives, with foods high in fat,
OL,15,Fsalt and sugar being the only group to
OL,16,Fhave seen a price drop in the last
OL,17,Fyear, the Food Foundation's Broken
OL,18,FPlate report, funded by the Nuffield
OL,19,FFoundation, said.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G1/9
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,305,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30402
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F304A1781067873
OL,3,CPoorest families must spend 85% of
OL,4,Cdisposable income to get healthy diet
OL,5,C` study
OL,7,FProtein foods saw the largest annual
OL,8,Fincrease in price at 4%, followed by
OL,9,Ffruit and vegetables at 1.7%.
OL,11,FMeanwhile, fast-food outlets make up a
OL,12,Fquarter of places to buy food in
OL,13,FEngland, rising to more than one in
OL,14,Fthree in the most deprived areas.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/9
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
