PN,30408
SC,0008
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F304A1781067873
OL,3,CPoorest families must spend 85% of
OL,4,Cdisposable income to get healthy diet
OL,5,C` study
OL,7,F"However, with the cost of everyday
OL,8,Fessentials remaining persistently
OL,9,Fhigh, healthy food is still out of
OL,10,Freach for many families ` and those
OL,11,Fliving in poverty often face greater
OL,12,Fchallenges in buying, preparing and
OL,13,Faccessing good food.
OL,15,F"With prices rising, we call on
OL,16,Fgovernment to make sure that all
OL,17,Fchildren receive the nutrition they
OL,18,Fneed regardless of their
OL,19,Fcircumstances."
OL,26,@oD@AOUwD@AOU{D@OO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G8/9
