PN,30409
SC,0009
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F304A1781067873
OL,3,CPoorest families must spend 85% of
OL,4,Cdisposable income to get healthy diet
OL,5,C` study
OL,7,FSonia Pombo, head of research and
OL,8,Fimpact at Action on Salt & Sugar,
OL,9,Fsaid: "This new report lays bare the
OL,10,Freality facing millions of families in
OL,11,Fthat healthy food is increasingly
OL,12,Funaffordable while products high in
OL,13,Ffat, salt and sugar remain cheap,
OL,14,Fheavily promoted and far too widely
OL,15,Favailable.
OL,17,F"When households with children on the
OL,18,Flowest incomes need to spend 85% of
OL,19,Ftheir disposable income to afford a
OL,20,Fhealthy diet, we cannot pretend this
OL,21,Fis simply about personal choice."
OL,26,@qD@GOUyD@AOU}D@aO]
